"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn.heatmap function is not suitable for visualizing a DataFrame like 'tips' directly. The heatmap function expects a matrix-like input, typically a 2D array or DataFrame with numerical values. The 'tips' DataFrame contains categorical data which is not suitable for a heatmap.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n<g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n># Example of a correct usage of seaborn with the 'tips' dataset\\n>g = sns.heatmap(tips.corr(), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n\"\n}"